Former NYC Atty, 2 Others Charged In $5M Escrow Heist
By Suevon Lee
Law360, Los Angeles (May 2, 2016, 11:13 PM ET) -- A disbarred Manhattan attorney, his brother and a third man conspired to steal and launder $5 million from attorney escrow accounts over a six-year period to pay for a house and living expenses, Manhattan prosecutors said Monday.Ex-lawyer David Katz, 62, his brother Jay Katz, 68, and Eli Luski, 53, were indicted on charges that included grand larceny and conspiracy, Manhattan District Attorney Cyrus R.Vance Jr. said.The trio allegedly stole hefty sums from accounts held in trust for various attorneys clients and then laundered the...
